The paper discusses the application of Bayesian optimization and Bayesian quadrature to reinforcement learning problems, which are typically addressed in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on finding a robust policy suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and experimental results suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the mathematical optimization (cs.MA) sub-category.
